<h2>Vision Changes: The Most Concerning</h2>

<p><strong>What it is:</strong> Blurred vision, light sensitivity, visual "snow" or halos around lights</p>
<p><strong>Why it happens:</strong> Enclomiphene affects estrogen receptors in the retina</p>
<p><strong>Frequency:</strong> Rare (under 5%), usually reversible</p>

<div style="background: #fef2f2; border-left: 4px solid #ef4444; border-radius: var(--r); padding: 20px; margin: 24px 0;">
  <p style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px;">⚠️ If You Experience Vision Changes</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>STOP enclomiphene immediately</strong></li>
    <li>See an ophthalmologist within 48 hours</li>
    <li>Most cases resolve within 2-4 weeks after stopping</li>
    <li>Do NOT restart enclomiphene—switch to HCG or traditional TRT</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h2>Mood Swings & Emotionality</h2>

<p><strong>Most common side effect (10-15%):</strong></p>
<ul style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li>Increased emotionality, crying more easily</li>
  <li>Anxiety or irritability</li>
  <li>Mood swings (highs and lows)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Why it happens:</strong> Enclomiphene can increase estradiol (E2) along with testosterone. High E2 causes mood issues.</p>

<p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
<ol style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li><strong>Check estradiol levels</strong> at week 8 (should be 20-40 pg/mL)</li>
  <li><strong>Lower enclomiphene dose</strong> (25mg → 12.5mg)</li>
  <li><strong>Add low-dose AI</strong> if E2 above 50 pg/mL (0.25-0.5mg anastrozole 2x/week)</li>
</ol>

<h2>Gynecomastia (Breast Tissue Growth)</h2>

<p><strong>Risk: 5-10% of men</strong></p>
<p><strong>Cause:</strong> Enclomiphene stimulates both testosterone AND estrogen. If estrogen rises too much relative to testosterone, breast tissue can develop.</p>

<p><strong>Early signs:</strong></p>
<ul style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li>Nipple sensitivity or tenderness</li>
  <li>Small lump under nipple (pea-sized)</li>
  <li>Breast tissue feels different</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Action plan:</strong></p>
<ol style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li><strong>Check estradiol immediately</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Add AI</strong> (anastrozole 0.5mg 2x/week)</li>
  <li><strong>Lower enclomiphene dose</strong> or stop temporarily</li>
  <li><strong>If caught early,</strong> tissue usually shrinks within 4-8 weeks</li>
</ol>

