<h2>Managing Side Effects</h2>

<p><strong>General strategies:</strong></p>

<ol style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li><strong>Start low:</strong> 12.5mg 2x/week minimizes side effects</li>
  <li><strong>Monitor estradiol:</strong> Check at week 8, keep 20-40 pg/mL</li>
  <li><strong>Don't chase high T:</strong> 600-800 ng/dL is optimal (minimize side effects)</li>
  <li><strong>Add AI only if needed:</strong> Don't prophylactically crash estrogen</li>
  <li><strong>Stop if vision changes:</strong> Non-negotiable—switch protocols</li>
</ol>

<h2>When to Stop Enclomiphene</h2>

<p><strong>Immediately stop if:</strong></p>
<ul style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li>Vision changes (any amount)</li>
  <li>Severe mood issues (depression, anxiety attacks)</li>
  <li>Gyno progressing despite AI</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Consider switching if:</strong></p>
<ul style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li>Persistent headaches or mood swings</li>
  <li>Testosterone response inadequate (under 400 ng/dL on 25mg)</li>
  <li>Already had kids and want simpler protocol (switch to TRT)</li>
</ul>

